                        <td align="left" width="90%" style="text-align:justify; padding-right:8px; background-color:white;font-size:1.0em;font-weight:400;" colspan="3">I Know How to Cover a Portland Protest. So Why Am I Shaking? <span style="font-weight:700;color:red;"> PORTLAND POLICE </span>officers in downtown
                            Portland in the early hours of July 18. This essay by Karina Brown, a Portland native and
                            Courthouse News reporter, was first published by Courthouse News on July 21. It's being
                            shared here with the permission of both the author and publication. </td>
